        "summary": "The real boss fight of learning Finnish: the moment you hesitate, a friendly Finn switches to English. They mean well - so push back politely. Ask for a repeat, ask for slower, and say you want the practice. Finns respect the effort, and most will happily stay in Finnish once you ask.",
